  "prompt": "Who is Margaret Hill Morris?",
  "response": "Margaret Hill Morris (1863\u20131938) was a prominent American social activist and suffragist based in New Jersey. She was known for her work in various social reform movements, particularly those related to women's rights and suffrage. Morris was involved in the New Jersey Woman Suffrage Association and played a significant role in advocating for women's voting rights during the early 20th century.\n\nIn addition to her suffragist activities, she was active in promoting other reforms, including issues related to education and labor rights. Her contributions to the women's suffrage movement in New Jersey were part of the broader national effort that ultimately led to the passage of the 19th Amendment to the U.S. Constitution in 1920, granting women the right to vote.\n\nIf you are looking for more specific information about her life or contributions, please let me know!",
